findInterfaceHandlerForInterface

AbstractInterfaceHandler findInterfaceHandlerForInterface(Interface interfaze)
Returns the AbstractInterfaceHandler for the kind of the specified interface or returns null if the interface has no kind. The handler provides information about the interface kind that could be presented to an end user. If no interface handler supports the interface kind, null is returned.

Parameters:
interfaze - the interface whose handler is returned
Returns:
the handler for the specified interface

findInterfaceHandlersForObject

AbstractInterfaceHandler[] findInterfaceHandlersForObject(java.lang.Object forObject)
Returns an array of AbstractInterfaceHandler for the object specified. Think of this as a bottom-up approach. It returns an array of AbstractInterfaceHandler which can create an Interface starting from the object passed. The enablement expression specified during the extension definition should match the object specified. The handler returned provides information about the implementation kind that could be presented to an end user. If no interface handler supports the object passed, null is returned.

Parameters:
forObject - the object from which an Interface can get created (bottom-up approach)
Returns:
the handler for the specified object
